crate.name: tokio
crate.description:
An event-driven, non-blocking I/O platform for writing asynchronous I/O
backed applications.

categories.description: Crates dealing with higher-level network protocols such as FTP, HTTP, or SSH, or lower-level network protocols such as TCP or UDP.
Crates to help you deal with events independently of the main program flow, using techniques like futures, promises, waiting, or eventing.
